com.esri.mo2.cs.geod
Interface Unit

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, Equivalency, GeodeticObject, NamedObject, PEObject
All Known Implementing Classes:
AngularUnit, BaseUnit, DMAngularUnit, DMSAngularUnit, FactorBasedUnit, LinearUnit
public interface Unit
extends NamedObject, GeodeticObject, PEObject, Equivalency

A Unit is either a linear or angular unit which defines a conversion to and from the MKS system. The extended MKS system herein uses meters and radians(not normally in MKS) as base systems. The following are example linear unit and the angular unit tables within the geodetic database:

  • [$Angular Units$, GenericFactory]
  • DEGREE, "Decimal Degrees", "", AngularUnit, "deg", 0.0174532925199433, 8
  • GON, "Gons", "", AngularUnit, "gon", 0.01745329251994, 8
  • GRAD, "Grads", "", AngularUnit, "grads", 0.01570796326794897, 8
  • MINUTE, "Minutes", "", AngularUnit, "minutes", .0002908882086657216, 8
  • DMS, "Degrees.MinutesSeconds", "", DMSAngularUnit, "dms", 8
  • DM, "Degrees.Minutes", "", DMAngularUnit, "dm", 8
  • RADIAN, "Radians", "", AngularUnit, "rads", 1.0, 8
  • MICRORADIAN, "MicroRadians", "", AngularUnit, "microrads", 0.001, 8
  • SECOND, "Seconds", "", AngularUnit, "secs", .00000484813681109536, 3
